        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 10:27PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1027 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Barfield, or 7 miles northeast of Lineville, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lineville, Lake Wedowee, Morrison Cross Roads, Barfield, Fosters
Cross Roads, Delta, Corinth, Hollis Crossroads, Newell, Ofelia,
Micaville, Chalafinnee, and Camp Sequoyah.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
